<div id="review_3373175141" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3373175141" />
    <a title="Janelle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle"><img alt="Janelle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581393896p2/88713906.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3373175141?book_show_action=true">Jun 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janelle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janelle" href="/user/show/88713906-janelle">Janelle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=library">library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/88713906-janelle?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3373175141" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12797086721798868519">Oh this was so good! Great characters, great story, great writing. In this book Kate Atkinson pulls together all the different threads of her story so well. It follows four different characters to start and you’re not sure how they will all intersect. Jackson is his usual put upon self, I’m not sure why he works as a central character but he does. The other main characters, Louise and the other police around her (particularly Marcus) and her new husband is one thread. Then we have Dr Hunter who </span>
  <span id="freeText12797086721798868519" style="display:none">Oh this was so good! Great characters, great story, great writing. In this book Kate Atkinson pulls together all the different threads of her story so well. It follows four different characters to start and you’re not sure how they will all intersect. Jackson is his usual put upon self, I’m not sure why he works as a central character but he does. The other main characters, Louise and the other police around her (particularly Marcus) and her new husband is one thread. Then we have Dr Hunter who has a tragedy in her childhood. And lastly Reggie Chase, a clever 16yo orphan, my favourite in this book. A lot of the subject matter is nasty crime, accidents and misfortunes for the various people in it but it’s a satisfying, enjoyable read! </span>
  <a data-text-id="12797086721798868519" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


